description.narrative: UNICEF continued providing leadership to the WASH cluster, managing core pipeline supplies, coordination and information management for better preparedness and response, prepositioning and distribution to about 62 WASH partners, reaching over 140,000 emergency-affected people. Progress was also made in building capacity for humanitarian response, promoting better integration between humanitarian and resilience of the communities including ensuring improved gender outcomes through women leadership positions and redressal mechanism in POCs. While UNICEF remains focused on delivering critical lifesaving WASH services to vulnerable populations,, access to many of the locations remains a problem due to conflict, lack of roads, and inhospitable terrain. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
